2.11pm South Africa have been dismissed for 326. The ball decked around more after the light drizzle. Bavuma popped a catch to point in the second over after lunch to give Mennie his maiden Test scalp. Hazlewood then carved his way through the lower order and ended with a six-for. Philander made a cameo for the visitors, hitting 32 off 28 balls. He will have a bigger role to play with the new ball. And tea has been pushed back to 3.30pm because of the rain delay. Be back soon for Australia's second dig.

1.30pm Buh-bye rain, at least for now. Welcome back, folks. Bavuma has faced 201 balls, four more than Australia had done in their entire innings. His 74* and de Kock's second Test hundred has ground Australia to dust.

1.20pm The covers are off, and bright sunshine means we'll be back quickly. Yes, play to resume at 1.30pm

Anirudh: "I think du Plessis must also mind the rain game involved and declare aggressively so that they can get 2-0 lead by bowling out Aussies "

1.12pm "Looks like the drizzle has stopped, and the rope is going around the field," says Firdose. "We should be back soon."

1pm It's drizzling lightly, says our correspondent Firdose Moonda from Bellerive Oval. "Covers on the pitch only."

12.30pm That's lunch. South Africa added 117 runs for the loss of de Kock in 37 overs in an extended morning session. There was not much lateral movement for Australia's seamers, both with the old ball and the new one. Bavuma dug in again, while de Kock was more aggressive. They also rotated the strike well during the 144-run stand for the sixth wicket. De Kock pressed on to convert a fifth successive fifty into a second Test ton, before Hazlewood bowled him through the gate for 104 off 143 balls. Bavuma is still unbeaten on 74, and South Africa lead by 203. We'll be back in 40 minutes.

By contrast, many of South Africa's players - those not taking part in the ODIs at home - were able to play first-class cricket during this period, and then had two warm-up matches in contrast to the one (pink ball) Shield game played before the Perth Test.
